title: wakui_rumi
body:
An [i][[iDOLMASTER Cinderella Girls|iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls]][/i] character in the Cool (Blue Diamond) category.Rumi is a woman who sacrificed her personal life to put an office career before everything else. She avoided having a social life to dedicate herself to work advancement, and even cut her hair to a boyish length because she didn't want being feminine to be a career issue. Her ambition led her to become a company manager, but also forced her into being single.
 
Rumi is often seen caring for her fellow idols, and takes on an almost motherly tone with [[Mukai Takumi]] and [[Wakabayashi Tomoka]]. Her love of cats often appears to get the best of her, causing her to have allergic reactions during lessons. She proves that she’s an extremely good tennis player, playing a competitive match that lasted well over an hour and 30 minutes with the Producer. Believing that she has lost her concentration she attempts to focus on flower arranging, but feels at a loss when she passes on the opportunity to pet a cat. Despite being allergic to them, Rumi really loves cats and can't avoid hugging them when she sees one.

title: journey
body:
[[Journey]] is a video game developed by "Thatgamecompany":http://thatgamecompany.com/ exclusively for the [[PlayStation 3]] and which is distributed on the PlayStation Network. Its Japanese title is 風ノ旅ビト ([i]Kaze no Tabibito[/i], lit. Traveler of the Wind).
The game features [[traveler (journey)|the player]] as a robed figure in a vast desert, journeying towards a mountain in the distance.
Along the way the player can meet other players on the same journey; the two players can assist each other, but cannot communicate via speech or text and are not shown each others' names until after completion. 
The game was released on March 7, 2012 for PlayStation Plus subscribers, and was fully released on March 13. 

h4. See Also:

title: warlic
body:
[b]Warlic[/b], also known as [b]the Blue Mage[/b] is a character that is part of the [[artix_entertainment|Artix Entertainment]] universe. He is considered the most powerful wielder of magic in all of Lore. He is a recurrent character in [[dragonfable|DragonFable]], where he was once killed by Nythera, his apprentice, but he laters come back; he helps The Hero many times throughout the game. In [[adventurequest_worlds|AdventureQuest Worlds]] he owns a magic shop in Battleon Town, where he sells a lot of things; he's also a major character during the [b]13 Lords of Chaos saga[/b]. He also appears in [[adventurequest|AdventureQuest]].

[spoiler]It is later revealed that he was actually an infernal but he didn't desire destruction like the others. He then rebelled against his father, pushing him off a cliff and thus, he was descended from his original state to a Human/Infernal hybrid.[/spoiler]

Han'eri (半襟, はんえり) is a decorative piece of cloth worn over a juban collar to add style or color to an outfit. About 16.5cm (6") wide by 110cm (43") long. Also added to protect the juban collar, as it's easily removable for washing.

title: help:text_syntax
body:
When searching by text, the following variation in search parameters may be used.

h5. Direct comparisons

These take the text field in its entirety when making the comparison as selected by the qualifier. The following qualifiers are available.

* (No qualifier) - Direct equality comparison.
* [code]*_eq[/code] - Same as above.
* [code]*_not_eq[/code] - Direct inequality comparison.
* [code]*_like[/code] - Equality comparison, supports the wildcard "*".
* [code]*_ilike[/code] - Same as above, though with case-insensitivity.
* [code]*_not_like[/code] - Inequality comparison, supports the wildcard "*".
* [code]*_not_ilike[/code] - Same as above, though with case-insensitivity.
* [code]*_regex[/code] - Regex equality comparison, follows Postgres' ERE regex formatting rules.
* [code]*_not_regex[/code] - Regex inequality comparison, follows Postgres' ERE regex formatting rules.

h5. Array comparisons

These break up the text field allowing multiple comparisons at once, either using the URL array format or a certain text separator. The following qualifiers are available.

* [code]*_array[/code] - Uses the URL array format making direct equality comparisons.
** Example: [code]search[name_array][]=foo&search[name_array][]=bar[/code]
* [code]*_comma[/code] - Uses a comma to break up the text field.
* [code]*_space[/code] - Uses a space to break up the text field.

[b]Note:[/b] A lowercase transformation will be applied on both sides of the equality comparison on search parameters that use the "lower" qualifier, e.g. [code]search[name_lower_comma]=Foo,Bar[/code]

h5. All parameter variations

For the following, [code]NAME[/code] is the name of the record field being searched for.

* [code]NAME[/code]
* [code]NAME_eq[/code]
* [code]NAME_not_eq[/code]
* [code]NAME_like[/code]
* [code]NAME_not_like[/code]
* [code]NAME_ilike[/code]
* [code]NAME_not_ilike[/code]
* [code]NAME_regex[/code]
* [code]NAME_not_regex[/code]
* [code]NAME_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_comma[/code]
* [code]NAME_space[/code]
* [code]NAME_lower_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_lower_comma[/code]
* [code]NAME_lower_space[/code]

h4. See also

title: mirana_(dota)
body:
[b]Mirana the Princess of the Moon[/b] is a playable character in [[Dota 2]].

h4. Trivia

* In the transition from [[defense_of_the_ancients|DotA]] to [[Dota 2]], various aspects of [b]Mirana[/b]'s character have been changed to avoid reference to Blizzard intellectual property.
** The names of two of Mirana's abilities were changed; Starstorm was previously called Starfall and Sacred Arrow was called Elune's Arrow.
** Her [[defense_of_the_ancients|DotA]] hero title was "[b]Priestess of the Moon[/b]", a class within the [[Warcraft]] universe. Her title was changed during the beta to her current, [b]Princess of the Moon[/b]. However, her voice lines remained unchanged, referring to herself still as the Priestess.
* In addition to the above changes, [b]Mirana[/b]'s surname - "[b]Nightshade[/b]" - was also dropped, so that she is known simply as "[b]Mirana[/b]".
* [b]Mirana[/b] is the tiger of the Multan Fort that killed the king of Mongols (in the Mongol folklore).
* Her mount's name is Sagan. Her response "Carl meet Sagan." is a pun on [b]Carl Sagan[/b].
* She appears to be wearing the Circlet item, which fits the item description as being "designed for human princesses".

title: starfleet_uniform
body:
A uniform from Starfleet, from the [[Star Trek]] universe. There are actually variations per series/film in the franchise.

h5. [i]The Original Series[/i] (includes the Mirror Universe)
[tn]See post #4633403, left side.[/tn]

In the TOS, set in the 2250s to the early 2270s, the standard duty uniform consists of a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[tunic]] with rank insignia sleeve stripes, color-coded by division (gold = command, red = operations, blue = sciences/medics), black [[undershirt]]s, black pants, and black [[boots]]. Captains wore a green-yellow wraparound tunic similar to East Asian clothing. Female uniforms were of a single tunic/[[miniskirt]] combo with [[pantyhose]].

[tn]See post #5449483 for Mirror Universe.[/tn]

In the episode [i]Mirror, Mirror[/i], the Terran Empire uniform is similar, replacing the Starfleet delta insignia with the sword-and-globe imperial insignia and adding a gold [[sash]] belt. Female uniforms consisted of a [[tank top]], black [[midriff]] undershirt, [[miniskirt]], and [[thighhighs|thighhigh]] boots.

h5. [i]The Next Generation[/i]
[tn]See post #1121461.[/tn]

The TNG, set in the 2350s, has a different version of the uniform: a black [[jumpsuit]] with the assigned color of division in front (red = command, gold = operations, blue = sciences), Starfleet insignia on the left breast side, rank insignia on the right [[collar]].

h5. J.J. Abrams' [i]Kelvin Timeline[/i] films
[tn]See post #4633403, right side.[/tn]

Similar to the TOS but updated to have solid rank sleeve stripes and darker color shades.

h4. External links
* "Memory Alpha/Star Trek Wikia article":[https://memory-alpha.fandom.com/wiki/Starfleet_uniform]

title: agano_(cruiser)
body:
"Agano":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_cruiser_Agano is the lead ship of the [i]Agano[/i]-class light cruisers.  Completed in October 31st of 1942, and was sunk by the submarine [i]USS Skate[/i] on February 16th 1944 while heading to Japan from Truk to receive repairs from damage in the Solomons campaign.  

They were among the last light cruisers the IJN ever developed, and were heavier than most light cruisers, but were consequently under-armed and under-armored for their weight, as the IJN did not increase those capabilities as much as the mass.  The Agano class was characteristic for having only a single [[smokestack]], as the light cruiser design was re-evaluated to have less clutter on the decks, be less overweight for its hull, and hence, have better stability in open seas.

In real life, Agano and her sisters were to have replaced the aging [i]Tenryuu[/i], [i]Kuma[/i], and [i]Nagara[/i] classes of light cruisers as destroyer squadron and submarine squadron flagships. Only her sisters Noshiro and Yahagi were able to fulfill that said role, however.
She was completed in mid-1942 and thrown into the front lines of the Guadalcanal and Solomons campaigns, eventually seeing action in the battle of Empress Augusta Bay on 2 November 1943. Just a few days later, she sustained severe damage from an air attack by US carriers and was forced to withdraw to Truk.

Not fully repaired, she was again attacked by US naval forces in Truk on February 1944 and sunk while retreating to Japan, with the destroyer Oite rescuing more than 500 survivors. The next day, Oite herself was sunk with all of the Agano survivors.

title: bouquet_toss
body:
A western [[wedding]] tradition where the [[bride]] tosses their wedding [[bouquet ]] to the unmarried women attending.  The woman who catches the bouquet is said to be the one who will be wed next.

The [[garter toss]] is the counterpart tradition for the groom and bachelors attending.

title: garter_toss
body: A western [[wedding]] tradition which involves two parts.  During the first part the [[bride]] sits on a chair and the [[groom]] then goes under her skirt to remove one of her garters either by hand or by tradition with his teeth.  The second part is the garter toss, where the garter is then tossed to the bachelors attending the wedding.  The bachelor who catches the garter is said to be the next person who'd become wed.  The garter toss is the counterpart to the bride's [[bouquet toss]].

title: adon_(street_fighter)
body:
[b]Adon[/b] ([i]katakana[/i]: [b]アドン[/b], [i]thai[/i]: [b]อาดอน[/b]) is a character from the [[Street Fighter]] series of fighting games. He has appeared in the first Street Fighter game, and notably the [[Street Fighter Zero (series)|Street Fighter Zero]] series. Adon also appears in [[street_fighter_iv_(series)|Super Street Fighter IV]].

Adon became [[sagat|Sagat's]] student three years after Sagat became God of Muay Thai. Frequently likened to a "lesser version of Sagat", even though he has strived to differentiate himself with more acrobatic techniques, Adon enters the first World Warrior tournament to prove he is more than that. The cocky Adon lets his guard down when he faces [[ryu (street fighter)|Ryu]], who takes him out with a single [[Shouryuuken]]. Afterwards, Ryu goes on to defeat Sagat, which leads to Adon's eventual breakdown. 

Adon is not mad at Ryu for defeating him, he is mad at Sagat for being unable to uphold Muay Thai's honor (conveniently forgetting how Ryu had bested him during the World Warrior tournament). He challenges Sagat for the title of God of Muay Thai and wins, but the enraged Sagat does so much damage to him in the fight that Adon has to be hospitalized for months. Adon's injuries eventually heal and a new fighter captivates his attention. Rumor reaches his ears of a fighter who has mastered the power that had enabled Ryu to win the first World Warrior Tournament. This fighter kills a man who was about to challenge Adon for his title. Adon sees this as a challenge. Knowing only that this [[akuma (street fighter)|mysterious fighter has red hair and wears a black gi with the symbol "Ten" on his back]], Adon swears to find him and test his strength.

title: carcano_m91/38
body:
After the Great War and the second war in Ethiopia, the Italian military eagerly searched for a new cartridge to replace the middling performance of 6.5x52mm Carcano. Aiming for higher penetration, flatter trajectory, and more damage, the Italians would ultimately come to the 7.35x51mm Carcano cartridge. This cartridge featured a Spitzer-style projectile instead of the 6.5 Carcano's round-nosed projectile. Using the same en-bloc clip-fed bolt-action design of the M91 Carcano, other notable changes in the M38 were cutting overall length by over ten inches and fixing the rear sights at a 200 meter distance, believing this would the average engagement distance in modern warfare.

Despite this ambition, the switch to 7.35 Carcano would become to strenuous and costly on logistics. Another issue included the Italian military's decision to chop the barrel of existing M1891s into M38s, ignoring how the old twist rate would affect the accuracy of the rifle with the newer, hotter ammunition, proving a detriment to a number of the rifles' accuracy. By mid 1940 the military would revert back to 6.5 Carcano, rebarreling most M38s with the few remaining 7.35 Carcano rifles relegated to auxiliary troops and paramilitary organizations. Under the new M91/38s designation, the rifle would continue production in Italy's earlier caliber of choice.

The M38 Carcano would serve as the backbone of the Italian army for much of World War II, though they weren’t shy about offering them to allies. Finland would accept many during the Winter War against the Soviet Union. Germany’s Afrika Corps would procure some M38s for themselves, rechambering them for 7.92x57mm Mauser. They would see combat throughout the Mediterranean and Eastern Fronts. Following the ousting of Benito Mussolini in 1943, some Italian troops in areas such as Greece and Yugoslavia would join the rebel troops and fight off the Germans. Since the end of World War II, these rifles have found their way into the hands of rebels and insurgents alike, seen most recently in conflicts such as the Libyan Civil War.

Since the end of the War, the Carcano has been a popular choice on the consumer market, particularly with hunting. With the short length, light weight, and the ability to mount an aftermarket scope on the rifle it was common to see it in the hands of hunters in the following decades alongside other wartime rifles.

title: cicada
body:
A large [[bug|insect]] belonging to the superfamily [i]Cicadoidea[/i]. Notable for their large, veiny transparent wings and their loud droning mating call.

In Japan the presence and droning cries of the cicada is heavily associated with summer (particularly on hot days with muggy weather). As such the cicada or its call is often used to help set the scene for a story happening during summer. In North America, periodic cicadas are famous for appearing in huge numbers in regular intervals.

An [[original]] character from the chinese game called [[gyee]]

He is a black-haired young man with a [[muscular]] build and short height, he comes from a tribe from the forest and wants to show them what is outside their tribe and stop being insolated. 
He usually wears a blue [[bandana]] on his head, abandaid on his nose and a multicolored [[necklace]] made of [[beads]], he have a jacket/shirt that use his tribe people but he have it wrapped on his waist, making him go topless, in his hands he wears a set of [[gauntlets]] and in one of his arms he also have an [[armband]], in his underbody he only have a short skirt, a white [[fundoshi]] and his bandages that cover part of his leg.
He have a knife as weapon, but he mostly use the martial arts that he learned in his tribe and also have the ability to control wind and energy, he prays to a entity called "Limuthule".

title: area_51
body:
Common nickname for a particular maximum-security [[United States Air Force|USAF]] research facility, situated within a large training range near [[Las Vegas]]. While it's known to have been previously used for high-tech aircraft development and Cold War espionage, the facility's [i]current[/i] purpose is a closely-guarded secret, which ironically makes it a very famous aspect of various conspiracy theories and general folklore around alien visitors to Earth.

In June 2019, a joke event known as ""Storm Area 51, They Can't Stop All Of Us":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storm_Area_51 " ostensibly scheduled a raid of the facility for September of that year, notoriously encouraging people to try and dodge bullets by using the [[Naruto Run]]. It became such a viral phenomenon that local law enforcement had to explicitly warn people to stay away for their own safety.

title: rodrigue_achille_fraldarius
body:
Character from [[Fire Emblem: Three Houses]]. Father of [[Felix Hugo Fraldarius]] and the late [[Glenn Fraldarius]], Rodrigue is Duke Fraldarius, the highest-ranking noble in all of Faerghus. He served as a right-hand man to the late King [[Lambert Egitte Blaiddyd]], who was also his best friend, and, since the latter's passing, as a father figure to [[Dimitri Alexandre Blaiddyd]]. [spoiler]No matter the route, Rodrigue never lives to see the end of the story.[/spoiler]

In [[Fire Emblem Warriors: Three Hopes|Three Hopes]], Rodrigue becomes a playable character on the [i]Azure Gleam[/i] route, appearing as a Cavalier.

[spoiler]Ever since the Tragedy of Duscur, Rodrigue has taken solace in the idea that his firstborn, Glenn, died like a true knight. This estranged Felix from him and marked the beginning of Felix's burning hatred for chivalry.[/spoiler]

A device designed to demonstrate the conservation of momentum. It consists of five spheres attached to a frame with wire. When one sphere on the end is lifted and released, its strike on the stationary spheres will transfer force to the opposite end, causing the last sphere to be forced upward.
